                      <span>1998-02-03</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I used this book with a first grade class during black history month.  The text is understandable for young minds and the pictures are beautifully illustrated, easily keeping the attention of a young class.  The only drawback is some of the language used to describe the whipping of slaves seemed harsh; caution should be used with sensitive children.  Otherwise, this book is very helpful and perfect for use with the primary grades.</span>
                  
              
